/*
==============================================================
ARRAY vs LINKED LIST (COMPARISON WITH EXPLANATION)
==============================================================

Feature              | Array                          | Linked List
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Memory               | Contiguous                     | Non-contiguous
                     | Stored in continuous block     | Nodes stored anywhere
                     | Easy address calculation       | Connected via pointers

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Access               | O(1) direct access             | O(n) sequential access
                     | arr[i] directly accessible     | Need to traverse from head

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Insertion            | O(n)                           | O(1) (if pointer known)
                     | Need to shift elements         | Just change links

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Deletion             | O(n)                           | O(1) (if pointer known)
                     | Shift elements again           | Skip node using pointers

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Size                 | Fixed                          | Dynamic
                     | Needs resizing                 | Grows/shrinks easily

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Memory Usage         | Less                           | More
                     | Only stores data               | Stores data + pointer(s)

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Cache Performance    | Good                           | Poor
                     | Better CPU cache usage         | Nodes scattered in memory

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Traversal            | Faster                         | Slower
                     | Continuous memory helps        | Pointer hopping slows down

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Implementation       | Easy                           | Complex
                     | Simple indexing                | Pointer management tricky

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Binary Search        | Possible                       | Not possible
                     | Because random access          | No direct indexing

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Flexibility          | Low                            | High
                     | Hard to modify structure       | Easy to insert/delete anywhere

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
QUICK MEMORY TRICK
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Array  → "Indexing king 👑" (fast access)

Linked List → "Pointer king 🔗" (fast modification)

==============================================================
*/